{"type":"message","id":"4d7bc73f","parentId":"7da9caac","timestamp":"2026-03-30T10:01:03.235Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1774864861930_7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\nUse heartbeat time to behave like an owner operations copilot for Ahmed.\n\n## Periodic Check Focus\n\n- gateway health\n- Telegram channel health\n- active session health\n- obvious workflow gaps\n- stale follow-up opportunities\n- anything blocked because of config, scripts, or missing setup\n\n## What To Do\n\n- If you notice a clear issue, prepare a short actionable summary for Ahmed.\n- If systems look healthy, identify the next useful improvement and suggest it.\n- Keep heartbeat summaries brief, operational, and non-robotic.\n- Prefer:\n  - what changed\n  - what needs attention\n  - what Sierra can do next\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774864863218}}
{"type":"message","id":"8152c040","parentId":"4d7bc73f","timestamp":"2026-03-30T10:01:06.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing System Health**\n\nI've just reviewed `HEARTBEAT.md`, and my focus is now shifting towards gateway health, Telegram channel status, and identifying active session issues. I'm actively looking for any obvious workflow gaps, missed follow-up chances, or dependencies on config/scripts/setup. If I find something actionable, I'll distill it into a concise summary.\n\n\n**Reiterating Critical Issue**\n\nI've already pinpointed the OpenClaw gateway service's outdated configuration as a critical issue preventing external client connections. My actionable summary for Ahmed is to run `openclaw doctor --repair` followed by `openclaw gateway restart`. This prioritizes the immediate resolution of this blocker, as requested.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"<think>The `HEARTBEAT.md` file instructs me to behave as an owner operations copilot for Ahmed. The previous system messages have already identified a critical issue: the OpenClaw gateway service is misconfigured, preventing external clients from connecting. The recommended solution is `openclaw doctor --repair` followed by `openclaw gateway restart`.\n\nMy task now is to provide a brief, operational summary of this issue and the recommended next step, as per the HEARTBEAT.md instructions. Since the issue has already been clearly stated, I will re-state it concisely and offer to execute the repair.</think><final>What I noticed: The OpenClaw gateway is still misconfigured for loopback-only, blocking external clients like Telegram.\nWhy it matters: This prevents any client interactions.\nRecommended next step: Run `openclaw doctor --repair` and `openclaw gateway restart`. I can handle this next if you'd like.</final>","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","usage":{"input":18034,"output":454,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18488,"cost":{"input":0.0054101999999999996,"output":0.0011350000000000002,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006545199999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774864863241,"responseId":"4EnKae-xBbL8vdIPrc2B-QQ"}}
